# Only public/ (the built Flutter web output) needs to reach Vercel. Everything
# else here is local Flutter/Dart tooling state or native-platform build
# output -- .gitignore covers these too, but Vercel's own upload step doesn't
# reliably honor it (confirmed: a deploy attempt uploaded 1.5GB, matching
# build/app + .dart_tool, and failed on Vercel's 100MB per-file limit), so
# this file makes the exclusion explicit rather than inferred.
build/
.dart_tool/
android/
ios/
web/
test/
integration_test/
docs/
.superpowers/
node_modules/
coverage/
*.iml

# api/ (the CORS-workaround proxy) is excluded as of the static-inventory-
# snapshot switch (docs/superpowers/specs/2026-07-20-static-inventory-
# snapshot-design.md) -- the app no longer calls it, so it's undeployed here
# rather than left live and unreachable-by-design. Source + tests stay in the
# repo as documented history (same treatment as InventoryApiClient/config.dart
# on the Flutter side); see docs/SPEC.md's "Data source (deviation)" note.
api/
